### [Proverbs Chapter 11](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#001.md)

[Proverbs 11:1](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">pro 11:1</span></span>

However men may make light of giving short weight or measure, and
however common such crimes may be, they are an abomination to the Lord.

[Proverbs 11:2](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">pro 11:2</span></span>

Considering how safe, and quiet, and easy the humble are, we see that
with the lowly is wisdom.

[Proverbs 11:3](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">pro 11:3</span></span>

An honest man's principles are fixed, therefore his way is plain.

[Proverbs 11:4](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">pro 11:4</span></span>

Riches will stand men in no stead in the day of death.

[Proverbs 11:5](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">pro 11:5</span></span>

The ways of wickedness are dangerous. And sin will be its own
punishment.

[Proverbs 11:7](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">pro 11:7</span></span>

When a godly man dies, all his fears vanish; but when a wicked man dies,
his hopes vanish.

[Proverbs 11:8](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#008.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_008">pro 11:8</span></span>

The righteous are often wonderfully kept from going into dangerous
situations, and the ungodly go in their stead.

[Proverbs 11:9](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">pro 11:9</span></span>

Hypocrites delude men into error and sin by artful objections against
the truths of God's word.

[Proverbs 11:10](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">pro 11:10</span></span>

Nations prosper when wicked men are cast down.

[Proverbs 11:12](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#012.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_012">pro 11:12</span></span>

A man of understanding does not judge of others by their success.

[Proverbs 11:13](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#013.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_013">pro 11:13</span></span>

A faithful man will not disclose what he is trusted with, unless the
honour of God and the real good of society require it.

[Proverbs 11:14](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#014.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_014">pro 11:14</span></span>

We shall often find it to our advantage to advise with others.

[Proverbs 11:15](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#015.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_015">pro 11:15</span></span>

The welfare of our families, our own peace, and our ability to pay just
debts, must not be brought into danger. But here especially let us
consider the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ in becoming Surety even for
enemies.

[Proverbs 11:16](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#016.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_016">pro 11:16</span></span>

A pious and discreet woman will keep esteem and respect, as strong men
keep possession of wealth.

[Proverbs 11:17](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">pro 11:17</span></span>

A cruel, froward, ill-natured man, is vexatious to those that are, and
should be to him as his own flesh, and punishes himself.

[Proverbs 11:18](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#018.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_018">pro 11:18</span></span>

He that makes it his business to do good, shall have a reward, as sure
to him as eternal truth can make it.

[Proverbs 11:19](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#019.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_019">pro 11:19</span></span>

True holiness is true happiness. The more violent a man is in sinful
pursuits, the more he hastens his own destruction.

[Proverbs 11:20](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#020.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_020">pro 11:20</span></span>

Nothing is more hateful to God, than hypocrisy and double dealing, which
are here signified. God delights in such as aim and act with
uprightness.

[Proverbs 11:21](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#021.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_021">pro 11:21</span></span>

Joining together in sin shall not protect the sinners.

[Proverbs 11:22](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#022.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_022">pro 11:22</span></span>

Beauty is abused by those who have not discretion or modesty with it.
This is true of all bodily endowments.

[Proverbs 11:23](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#023.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_023">pro 11:23</span></span>

The wicked desire mischief to others, but it shall return upon
themselves.

[Proverbs 11:24](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#024.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_024">pro 11:24</span></span>

A man may grow poor by not paying just debts, not relieving the poor,
not allowing needful expenses. Let men be ever so saving of what they
have, if God appoints, it comes to nothing.

[Proverbs 11:25](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#025.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_025">pro 11:25</span></span>

Both in temporal and spiritual things, God commonly deals with his
people according to the measure by which they deal with their brethren.

[Proverbs 11:26](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#026.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_026">pro 11:26</span></span>

We must not hoard up the gifts of God's bounty, merely for our own
advantage.

[Proverbs 11:27](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#027.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_027">pro 11:27</span></span>

Seeking mischief is here set against seeking good; for those that are
not doing good are doing hurt, even to themselves.

[Proverbs 11:28](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#028.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_028">pro 11:28</span></span>

The true believer is a branch of the living Vine. When those that take
root in the world wither, those who are grafted into Christ shall be
fruitful.

[Proverbs 11:29](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#029.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_029">pro 11:29</span></span>

He that brings trouble upon himself and his family, by carelessness, or
by wickedness, shall be unable to keep and enjoy what he gets, as a man
is unable to hold the wind, or to satisfy himself with it.

[Proverbs 11:30](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#030.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_030">pro 11:30</span></span>

The righteous are as trees of life; and their influence upon earth, like
the fruits of that tree, support and nourish the spiritual life in many.

[Proverbs 11:31](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#031.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_031">pro 11:31</span></span>

Even the righteous, when they offend on earth, shall meet with sharp
corrections; much more will the wicked meet the due reward of their
sins. Let us then seek those blessings which our Surety purchased by his
sufferings and death; let us seek to copy his example, and to keep his
commandments.

